Author: Corey Thompson <coreyt@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 17 12:49:12 2026 -0500

    fix(11d-fix-1): release-gate dispatch handling + skip irreversible publish
    
    - verify-release-gates.sh now runs on workflow_dispatch as well as tag push.
      Tag/Cargo.toml lockstep check is skipped on dispatch (no v-tag exists);
      all other gates still enforced. Dispatch with dry_run=false emits an
      explicit emergency-republish warning to stderr (clean state still passes).
    - publish-pypi job is gated `if: inputs.dry_run != true`. TestPyPI also
      rejects same-version re-uploads, so dry-run rehearsals would consume the
      next release's version slot. build-python matrix still runs on dry-run
      for cross-platform wheel buildability signal.
